What We've Learned Updated: Customer wants assistance with setting up NEA
If this is an initial setup and not a migration, please involve the Account Owner as this may need to go to Professional Services for implementation.

@Frantz Baptiste​ please arrange an initial meeting to assess the extent of changes needed during this NEA migration - the customer seems to have moved all resources from DomainA to DomainB. If all resources were simply moved to the new domain there may not be much needed beyond a normal application migration.
Invitation updated. Attendees: Frantz Baptiste, Marc Payzant

The customer is not planning to migrate any data; he wants to create a new environment with a new DC and SQL server.

I explained to the customer that he would need to follow the new environment's guidelines to ensure proper permission is created for each server.

Since it's a new install, no migration is involved. I will close this ticket, and the customer will open a new ticket when ready to install NEA in the new server.
